Keywords: Chebyshev polynomials, function gradient descent algorithm, loss function, one-day-ahead forecast
Abstract: This paper proposes using Chebyshev polynomials to approximate time-varying parameters
of a GARCH model, where polynomial coefficients are estimated via numerical optimization
using the function gradient descent method. We investigate the asymptotic properties of the
estimates of polynomial coefficients and the subsequent estimate of conditional variance.
Monte Carlo studies are conducted to examine the performance of the proposed polynomial
approximation. With empirical studies of modelling daily returns of the US 30-year T-bond
daily closing price and daily returns of the gold futures closing price, we find that in terms of
in-sample fitting and out-of-sample forecasting, our proposed time-varying model outperforms 
the constant-parameter counterpart and a benchmark time-varying model.  
