Keywords: aggregation, coherence, hierarchical time series, reconciliation 
Abstract: The aim of this paper is to provide a thinking road-map and a practical
guide to researchers and practitioners working on hierarchical forecasting
problems. Evaluating the performance of hierarchical forecasts comes with
new challenges stemming from both the structure of the hierarchy and the
application context. We discuss several relevant dimensions for researchers
and analysts: the scale and units of the time series, the issue of sparsity,
the forecast horizon, the importance of multiple evaluation windows and the
multiple objective decision context. We conclude with a series of practical
recommendations.
